pull_request.title: Potential switchable RNG API
pull_request.body: Here is a potential switchable RNG API which could hopefully accommodate running the NIST KATs and the normal RNG within the same executable. I haven't yet implemented the NIST KAT DRBG. However this doesn't take the split secret/public RNG approach of s2n.

pull_request.title: Try changing algorithm identifiers to strings
pull_request.body: I was using an enum for algorithm identifiers, and some code assumed that these were sequential.  Assuming sequential means that if we want to remove an algorithm, we can't have gaps. So we'd have to reassign numbers.  But then this would mean binary incompatibility between different versions of liboqs nist-branch.  We also could not have binary compatibility with liboqs master (once master gets the new KEM API) because a different order of KEMs.  So I am trying strings for algorithm identifiers.

pull_request.title: OQS integration into OpenSSL's master TLS 1.3 code
pull_request.body:
This work-in-progress, initial PR integrates OQS into the OpenSSL 1.1.1 TLS 1.3 code (master branch). Only some KEX alg are integrated.

Next steps: adding more KEX schemes, enabling hybrid KEX, adding PQC auth, supporting TLS 1.2.

See README.md for details.
